obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (43539)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43539&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1*** Works of Defence Act, 1903; and`
  line
  line `^2[(2) It extends to the whole of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "Indian" omitted by Act 50 of 1974, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-12-1974).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 39 of 1965, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 3-12-1965).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (43540)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43540&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is something repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "land" includes benefits to arise out of land, and things attached to the earth or`
  line `permanently fastened to anything attached to the earth;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression person interested includes all persons claiming an interest in compensation to be`
  line `made on account of the imposition of restrictions upon the use and enjoyment of land under this Act; and`
  line `a person shall be deemed to be interested in land if he is interested in an casement affecting the land;`
  line
  line `^1[(c) the expression "District" means one of the Districts into which India is, for military purposes for`
  line `the time being, divided; it includes a Brigade area which does not form part of any District, and any area`
  line `which the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a District for all`
  line `or any of the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the expression "Central Officer Commanding the District" means the officer for the time being in`
  line `command of the forces in a District;]`
  line
  line `(e) the expression "Commanding Officer" means the officer for the time being in command of a work`
  line `of defence;`
  line
  line `(f) the expression "Collector" includes any officer specially appointed by the ^2[Central Government]`
  line `to perform the functions of a Collector under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) the expression "Court" means a principal Civil Court of original jurisdiction, unless the ^2[CentralGovernment] has appointed (as it is hereby empowered to do) a special judicial officer within any`
  line `specified local limits to perform the functions of the Court under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) "maintain", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, does not, when used in`
  line `relation to a house or other construction, include the doing of any act necessary for keeping such house or`
  line `construction, until the making of the award referred to in section 12 or until the exercise, prior to the`
  line `making of the award, of the powers of demolition conferred, in case of emergency, by section 6, subsections (1) and (3), in the state in which it was at the time of the publication of the notice referred to in`
  line `section 3, sub-section (2);`
  line
  line `(i) the following persons shall be deemed "entitled to act" as and to the extent hereinafter provided,`
  line `that is to say,--`
  line
  line `trustees for other persons beneficially interested shall be deemed the persons entitled to act with`
  line `reference to any case, and that to the same extent as the persons beneficially interested could have`
  line `acted if free from disability;`
  line
  line `a married woman, in cases to which the English law is applicable, shall be deemed the person so`
  line `entitled to act, and, whether of full age or not, to the same extent as if she were unmarried and of full`
  line `age; and`
  line
  line `the guardians of minors and the committees or managers of lunatics or idiots shall be deemed`
  line `respectively the persons so entitled to act, to the same extent as the minors, lunatics or idiots`
  line `themselves, if free from disability, could have acted:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(i) no person shall be deemed "entitled to act" whose interest in the subject-matter is shown`
  line `to the satisfaction of the Collector or Court to be adverse to the interest of the person interested`
  line `for whom he would otherwise be entitled to act;`
  line
  line `(ii) in every case the person interested may appear by a next friend or, in default of his`
  line `appearance by a next friend, the Collector or Court, as the case may be, shall appoint a guardian`
  line `for the case to act on his behalf in the conduct thereof;`
  line
  line `(iii) the provisions of Chapter XXXI of the Code of Civil Procedure^3`
  line `(14 of 1882) shall,`
  line `mutatis mutandis, apply in the case of persons interested appearing before a Collector or Court by`
  line `a next friend, or by a guardian for the case, in proceedings under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(iv) no person "entitled to act" shall be competent to receive the compensation money`
  line `payable to the person for whom he is entitled to act, unless he would have been competent to`
  line `alienate the land upon the use and enjoyment of which restrictions are to be imposed and receive`
  line `and give a good discharge for the purchase-money on a voluntary sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1921, s. 2, for clauses (c) and (d).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `3. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), First Schedule, Order XXXII.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (43541)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Construction of references to laws not in force, or any functionary not in existence, in any area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 39 of 1965, s. 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43541&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Construction of references to laws not in force, or any functionary not in existence, in any`
  line `area.--Any reference in this Act to any law which is not in force in any area or any reference therein to any`
  line `functionary not in existence in any area shall, in relation to that area, be construed as a reference to the`
  line `corresponding law, if any, in force or to the corresponding functionary, if any, in existence, in that area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (43542)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Declaration and notice that restrictions will be imposed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43542&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it appears to the ^1[Central`
  line `Government] that it is necessary to impose restrictions upon the use and enjoyment of land in the vicinity of`
  line `any work of defence or of any site intended to be used or to be acquired for any such work, in order that such`
  line `land may be kept free from buildings and other obstructions, a declaration shall be made to that effect under`
  line `the signature of a Secretary to such Government or of some officer duly authorised to certify its orders.`
  line
  line `(2) The said declaration shall be published in the Official Gazette and shall state the district or other`
  line `territorial division in which the land is situate and the place where a sketch plan of the land, which shall be`
  line `prepared on a scale not smaller than six inches to the mile and shall distinguish the boundaries referred to in`
  line `section 7, may be inspected; and the Collector shall cause public notice of the substance of the said`
  line `declaration to be given at convenient places in the locality,`
  line
  line `(3) The said declaration shall be conclusive proof that it is necessary to keep the land free from buildings`
  line `and other obstructions.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (43543)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Power to do preliminary Acts after publication of notice under section 3, sub-section (2).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43543&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `It shall`
  line `be lawful for such officer as the ^1[Central Government] may, by general or special order, authorise in this`
  line `behalf, and for his servants and workmen, at any time after publication of the notice mentioned in section 3,`
  line `sub-section (2), to enter upon and survey and take levels of any land in such locality, to dig or bore into the`
  line `sub-soil, to do all other acts necessary to ascertain whether any and, if so, what restrictions should be imposed`
  line `on the use and enjoyment of the land, to set out the boundaries of the land upon the use and enjoyment of`
  line `which restrictions are to be imposed, or of any part of such land, to mark such levels, boundaries and line by`
  line `placing marks and cutting trenches, and, where otherwise the survey cannot be completed and the levels taken`
  line `and the boundaries and line marked, to cut down and clear away any part of any standing crop, fence or`
  line `jungle :`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall enter into any building or upon any enclosed court or garden attached to a`
  line `dwelling-house (unless with the consent of the occupier thereof) without previously giving such occupier at`
  line `least seven days' notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (43544)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Payment for damage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43544&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The officer so authorised shall at the time of such entry pay or tender`
  line `payment for all necessary damage to be done as aforesaid, and, in case of dispute as to the sufficiency of the`
  line `amount so paid or tendered, he shall at once refer the dispute to the decision of the Collector or other chief`
  line `revenue officer of the district, and such decision shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (43545)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Further powers exercisable after publication of notice under section 3, sub-section (2).`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43545&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Whenever a declaration has been made and public notice thereof has been given under section 3, it shall,`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-sections (2) to (4), be lawful for such officer as the ^1[Central Government]`
  line `may, by general or special order, authorise in this behalf, and for his servants and workmen, to enter and`
  line `demolish any buildings or other constructions on the surface, to cut down or grub up all or any of the trees, to`
  line `remove or alter all or any of the banks, fences, hedges and ditches, to make underground and other drains, to`
  line `fill up all excavations, and demolish all buildings and other constructions below the surface, and generally to`
  line `level and clear the said land and do all such acts for levelling and clearing the same as he may deem`
  line `necessary or, proper but in such manner nevertheless that evidence of the boundaries of the lands held by`
  line `different owners may be preserved.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers conferred by sub-section (1) shall not be exercised,--`
  line
  line `(a) save as otherwise provided by sub-section (3), before the making of the award hereinafter referred`
  line `to in section 12, nor`
  line
  line `(b) save as otherwise provided by sub-section (4), after the expiration of six months from the making`
  line `of the said award, or any shorter period on the expiration of which the officer exercising such powers`
  line `gives notice to the Collector that there will be no further exercise of them.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of emergency, the ^1[Central Government] ^2*** may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `declare that all or any powers conferred by sub-section (1) may be exercised at any time within six months`
  line `after the publication of the notice referred to in section 3, sub-section (2), and such powers may be exercised`
  line `accordingly, and the said notification shall be conclusive proof of emergency.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall be deemed to preclude any such officer or his servants or workmen`
  line `from exercising at any lime the said powers for the purpose of removing, wholly or in part, any building or`
  line `other obstruction maintained, created, added to, altered, planted, stacked, stored or otherwise accumulated in`
  line `contravention of this Act or of any rule or order made there under or of any condition prescribed in`
  line `accordance therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. The words "with the previous sanction of the G.G. in C." omitted 2i@ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (43546)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title Restrictions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43546&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `From and after the publication of the notice mentioned in section 3, sub-section (2),`
  line `such of the following restrictions as the ^1[Central Government] may in its discretion declare therein shall`
  line `attach with reference to such land, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Within an outer boundary which, except so far as is otherwise provided in section 39,`
  line `sub-section (4), may extend to a distance of two thousand yards from the crest of the outer parapet of the`
  line work,--
  line
  line `(i) no variation shall be made in the ground-level, and no building, wall, bank or other`
  line `construction above the ground shall be maintained, erected, added to or altered otherwise than with`
  line `the written approval of the ^2[General Officer Commanding the District], and on such conditions, as`
  line `he may prescribe;`
  line
  line `(ii) no wood, earth, stone, brick, gravel, sand or other material shall be stacked, stored or`
  line `otherwise accumulated:`
  line `Provided that, with the written approval of the ^3[General Officer Commanding the District] and`
  line `on such conditions as he may prescribe, road-ballast, manure and agricultural produce may be`
  line `exempted from the prohibition:`
  line
  line `Provided also that any person having control of the land as owner, lessee or occupier shall be`
  line `bound forthwith to remove such road-ballast, manure or agricultural produce, without compensation,`
  line `on the requisition of the Commanding Officer;`
  line
  line `(iii) no surveying operation shall be conducted otherwise than by or under the personal`
  line `supervision of a public servant duly authorised in this behalf, in the case of land under the control of`
  line `military authority, by the Commanding Officer and, in other cases, by the Collector with the`
  line `concurrence of the Commanding Officer; and`
  line
  line `(iv) where any building, wall, bank or other construction above the ground has been permitted`
  line `under clause (i) of this sub-section to be maintaind, erected, added to or altered, repairs shall not,`
  line `without the written approval of the ^2[General Officer Commanding the District], be made with`
  line `materials different in kind from those employed in the original building, wall, bank or other`
  line construction.
  line
  line `(b) Within a second boundary which may extend to a distance of one thousand yards from the crest of`
  line `the outer parapet of the work, the restrictions enumerated in clause (a) shall apply with the following`
  line `additional limitations, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i)^4[no building, wall, bank or other construction of permanent materials above the ground shall`
  line `be maintained otherwise than with the written approval of the General Officer Commanding the`
  line `District and on such conditions as he may prescribe, and no such building, wall bank or other`
  line `construction shall be erected:]`
  line
  line `Provided that, with the written approval of the ^5[General Officer Commanding the District] and`
  line `on such conditions as he may prescribe, huts, fences or other constructions of wood or other`
  line `materials, easily destroyed or removed, may be maintained, erected, added to or altered:`
  line
  line `Provided also, that any person having control of the land as owner, lessee or occupier shall be`
  line `bound forthwith to destroy or remove such huts, fences or other constructions, without compensation,`
  line `upon an order in writing signed by the ^6[General Officer Commanding the District]; and`
  line
  line `(ii) live hedges, rows or clumps or trees or orchards shall not be maintained, planted, added to or`
  line `altered otherwise than with the written approval of the ^5[General Officer Commanding the District]`
  line `and on such conditions as he may prescribe.`
  line
  line `(c) Within a third boundary which may extend to a distance of five hundred yards from the crest of`
  line `the outero parapet of the work, the restrictions enumerated in clauses (a) and (b) shall apply with the`
  line `following additional limitation, namely:--`
  line
  line `no building or other construction on the surface, and no excavation, building or other`
  line `construction below the surface, shall be maintained or erected :`
  line
  line `Provided that, with the written approval of the Commanding Officer and on such conditions as he`
  line `may prescribe, ^7[a building or other construction on the surface may be maintained and] open railings`
  line `and dry brush-wood fences may be exempted from this prohibition.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G"..`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 11 of 1921, s. 3, for "General Officer Commanding the Division".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "General Officer Commanding the Division, District or Brigade".`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 28 of 1940, s. 2, for certain words.`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 11 of 1921, s. 3, for "General Officer Commanding the Division".`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "General Officer Commanding the Division, District or Brigade".`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 2, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (43547)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Land to be marked out, measured, registered and planned.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43547&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the`
  line `publication of the declaration aforesaid, the Collector shall cause the land to be marked out and measured,`
  line `and shall also prepare a register and a detailed plan, which shall be on a scale not smaller than six inches to`
  line `the mile, showing accurately every building, tree and other obstruction.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (43548)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Notice to persons interested.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43548&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) At any time before the expiration of--`
  line
  line `(a) the period of eighteen months from the publication of the declaration referred to in section 3, or`
  line
  line `(b) such other period not exceeding three years from the said publication as the ^1[CentralGovernment] ^2*** may, by notification in the Official Gazette direct in this behalf,`
  line
  line `the Collector shall cause public notice to be given at convenient places on or near the land, stating the effect`
  line `of the said declaration and that claims to compensation for all interests in such land affected by anything done`
  line `or ordered in pursuance of such declaration may be made to him:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where anything has been done in exercise of the powers conferred, in case of emergency`
  line `by section 6, sub-section (3), the notice prescribed by this section shall be given as soon as may be thereafter.`
  line
  line `(2) Such notice shall state the particulars of any damage ordered to be done or, in the case referred to in`
  line `section 6, sub-section (3), done in exercise of any of the powers conferred by the said section, and the`
  line `particulars of any restrictions attaching to the land under section 7, and shall require all persons interested in`
  line `the land to appear personally or by agent before the Collector at a time and place therein mentioned (such`
  line `time not being earlier than fifteen days after the date of publication of the notice), and to state the nature of`
  line `their respective interests in the land and the amount and particulars of their claims to compensation for`
  line `damage to such interests and their objections (if any) to the measurements made under section 8. The`
  line `Collector may in any case require such statement to be made in writing and signed by the party or his agent.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector shall also serve notice to the same effect on the occupier (if any) of such land and on all`
  line `such persons known or believed to be interested therein, or to be entitled to act for persons so interested, as`
  line `reside or have agents authorised to receive service on their behalf, within the revenue-district in which the`
  line `land is situate.`
  line
  line `(4) In case any person so interested resides elsewhere, and has no such agent the notice shall be sent to`
  line `him by post in a letter addressed to him at his last known residence, address or place of business.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  line
  line `2. The words "with the previous sanction of the G.G. in C." rep, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (43549)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to require and enforce the making of statements as to names and interests.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43549&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line The
  line `Collector may also require any such person to make or deliver to him, at a time and place mentioned (such`
  line `time not being earlier than fifteen days after the date of the requisition) a statement containing, so far as may`
  line `be practicable, the name of every other person possessing any interest in the land or any part thereof as coproprietor, sub-proprietor, mortgagee, tenant or otherwise, and of the nature of such interest, and of the rents`
  line `and profits (if any) received or receivable on account thereof for three years next preceding the date of the`
  line statement.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (43550)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Application of certain sections of the Indian Penal Code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43550&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every person required to make or`
  line `deliver a statement under section 9 or section 10 shall be deemed to be legally bound to do so within the`
  line `meaning of sections 175 and 176 of the Indian Penal Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (43551)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Inquiry and award by Collector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43551&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `On the day fixed under section 9 or on any other day to which`
  line `the inquiry has been adjourned, the Collector shall proceed to inquire into the objections (if any) which any`
  line `person interested has stated pursuant to a notice given under the said section to the measurements made under`
  line `section 8, and into the decrease in the value of the land, and into the respective interests of the persons`
  line `claiming the compensation, and shall make an award under his hand of--`
  line
  line `(a) the true area of the land and the nature of the obstructions from which the land is to be kept free;`
  line
  line `(b) the compensation which in his opinion should be allowed for any damage caused or to be caused`
  line `under section 6 and for any restrictions imposed under section 7; and`
  line
  line `(c) the apportionment of the said compensation among all the persons known or believed to be`
  line `interested in the land, of whom or of whose claims he has information, whether they have respectively`
  line `appeared before him or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (43552)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Award of Collector when to be final.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43552&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Such award shall be filed in the Collector's office and`
  line `shall, except as hereinafter provided, be final and conclusive evidence, as between the Collector and the`
  line `persons interested; whether they have respectively appeared before the Collector or not, of the true area of the`
  line `land, the nature of the said obstruction from which the land is to be kept free, the damage caused or to be`
  line `caused under section 6, the value of the rights restricted under section 7 and the apportionment of the`
  line `compensation among the persons interested.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector shall give immediate notice of his award to such of the persons interested as are not`
  line `present personally or by their representatives when the award is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (43553)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Adjournment of inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43553&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The Collector may, for any cause he thinks fit, from time to time adjourn`
  line `the inquiry to a day to be fixed by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (43554)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power to summon and enforce attendance of witnesses and production of documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (Act 5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43554&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `For the`
  line `purpose of injuries under this Act the Collector shall have power to summon and enforce the attendance of`
  line `witnesses, including the parties interested or any of them, and to compel the production of documents, by the`
  line `same means, and (so far as may be) in the same manner, as is provided in the case of a Civil Court under the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure^1(14 of 1882).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (43555)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Matters to be considered and neglected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43555&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `In determining the amount of compensation, the`
  line `Collector shall be guided by the provisions contained in sections 23 and 24.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (43556)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Supplementary proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43556&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the officer exercising powers conferred by section 6`
  line `considers it necessary that anything in respect of which any person is or may be entitled to compensation but`
  line `of which do notice has been given or compensation awarded, under sections 9 and 12, respectively, should be`
  line `done in pursuance of the said powers, the collector shall cause supplementary notice to be given, as nearly as`
  line `may be, in the manner prescribed by section 9 and subject to the limit of time imposed by sub-section (1) of`
  line `that section, and the provisions of sections 10 to 16 shall, so far as they are applicable be deemed to apply to`
  line `any further inquiry and award which may be held or made in consequence of such supplementary notice.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (43557)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Reference to Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43557&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person interested who has not accepted the award may, by written`
  line `application to the Collector, require that the mailer be referred by the Collector for the determination of the`
  line `Court, whether his objection be to the measurement of the land, the amount of the compensation, the persons`
  line `to whom it is payable, or the apportionment of the compensation among the persons interested:`
  line
  line `Provided that every such application shall be made,--`
  line
  line `(a) if the person making it was present or represented before the Collector at the time when he made`
  line `his award, within six weeks from the date of the Collector's award;`
  line
  line `(b) in other cases, within six weeks of the receipt of the notice from the Collector under section 13;`
  line `sub-section (2) or within six months from the date of the Collectors award, whichever period shall first`
  line expire.
  line
  line `(2) The application shall state the grounds on which objection to the award is taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (43558)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Collector's statement to the Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43558&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) In making the reference the Collector shall state, for the`
  line `information of the Court, in writing under his hand--`
  line
  line `(a) the situation and extent of the land with particulars of any damage caused under section 6 or of`
  line `restrictions imposed under section 7;`
  line
  line `(b) the names of the persons whom he has reason to think interested in such land;`
  line
  line `(c) the amount of compensation awarded under section 12; and`
  line
  line `(d) if the objection be to the amount of the compensation, the grounds on which the amount of`
  line `compensation was determined.`
  line
  line `(2) To the said statement shall be attached a schedule giving the particulars of the notices served upon`
  line `and of the statements in writing made or delivered by, the parties interested respectively.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (43559)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Service of notice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43559&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Court shall thereupon cause a notice specifying the day on which the Court`
  line `will proceed to determine the objection, and directing their appearance before the Court on that day, to be`
  line `served on the following persons namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the applicant;`
  line
  line `(b) all persons interested in the objection, except such (if any) of them as have consented without`
  line `protest to receive payment of the compensation awarded; and`
  line
  line `(c) if the objection is in regard to the area of the land, the nature of the obstructions or the amount of`
  line `the compensation, the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (43560)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Restriction on scope of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43560&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The scope of the inquiry in every such proceeding shall be`
  line `restricted to a consideration of the interests of the persons affected by the objection.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (43561)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Proceedings to be in open Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43561&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every such proceeding shall take place in open Court, and all`
  line `persons entitled to practise in any Civil Court in the State shall be entitled to appear, plead and act, as the case`
  line `may be, in such proceeding.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (43562)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Matters to be considered in determining compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43562&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) In determining the amount of`
  line `compensation to be awarded for damage caused, or to be caused, or for restrictions imposed under this Act,`
  line `the Court shall take into consideration--`
  line
  line `(a) the actual decrease in market value of the land owing to the publication of the declaration relating`
  line `thereto under section 3 and any damage caused or to be caused under section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the damage sustained by the person interested, by reason of the removal of any standing crops in`
  line `the exercise of any power conferred by section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) the damage (if any) sustained by the person interested, by reason of ceasing to be able to use such`
  line `land conjointly with his other land;`
  line
  line `(d) the damage (if any) sustained by the person interested, by anything done or ordered under`
  line `sections 6 and 7 injuriously affecting his other property, movable or immovable, in any other manner, or`
  line `his earnings; and`
  line
  line `(e) if, in consequence of the imposition of restrictions, the person interested is compelled to change`
  line `his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses (if any) incidental to such change.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the amount representing the actual decrease in the market-value of the land as above`
  line `provided, the Court shall in every case award a further sum of fifteen per centum on such amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (43563)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Matters not to be considered in determining compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43563&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `In determining the amount of`
  line `compensation to be awarded for damage caused, or to be caused, or for restrictions imposed under this Act,`
  line `the Court shall not take into consideration--`
  line
  line `(a) the degree of urgency which has led to the damage or the imposition of restrictions;`
  line
  line `(b) any disinclination of the person interested to submit to damage or restrictions;`
  line
  line `(c) any damage sustained by him, which, if caused by a private person, would not render such person`
  line `liable to a suit;`
  line
  line `(d) any increase to the value of the other land of the person interested, accruing or likely to accrue`
  line `from anything done under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(e) any outlay or improvements on, or disposal of, the land commenced, made or effected without the`
  line `sanction of the Collector after the date of the publication of the declaration under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (43564)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Rules as to amount of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43564&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the applicant has made a claim to compensation,`
  line `pursuant to any notice given under section 9, the amount awarded to him by the Court shall not exceed the`
  line `amount so claimed or be less than the amount awarded, by the Collector under section 12.`
  line
  line `(2) When the applicant has refused to make such claim or has omitted without sufficient reason (to be`
  line `allowed by the Judge) to make such claim, the amount awarded by the Court shall in no case exceed the`
  line `amount awarded by the Collector.`
  line
  line `(3) When the applicant has omitted for a sufficient reason (to be allowed by the Judge) to make such`
  line `claim, the amount awarded to him by the Court shall not be less than, and may exceed, the amount awarded`
  line `by the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (43565)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Form of awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43565&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Every award under this Part shall be in writing signed by the Judge, and shall`
  line `specify the amount awarded under section 23, sub-section (1), clause (a), and also the amounts (if any)`
  line `respectively a warded under each of the other clauses of the same sub-section, together with the grounds of`
  line `awarding each of the said amounts.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (43566)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43566&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every such award shall also state the amount of costs incurred in the proceedings under`
  line `this Pan, and by what persons and in what proportion they are to be paid.`
  line
  line `(2) When the award of the Collector is not upheld, the costs shall ordinarily be paid by the Collector,`
  line `unless the Court is of opinion that the claim of the applicant was so extravagant or that he was so negligent in`
  line `putting his case before the Collector that some deduction from his costs should be made or that he should pay`
  line `a part of the Collector's costs.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (43567)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Collector may be directed to pay interest on excess compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43567&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `If the sum which, in the`
  line `opinion of the Court, the Collector ought to have awarded as compensation is in excess of the sum which the`
  line `Collector did award as compensation, the Court may direct that the Collector shall pay interest on such excess`
  line `at the rate of six per centum per annum from the date of his award to the date of payment of such excess into`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (43568)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Particulars of apportionment to be specified.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43568&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Where there are several persons interested, if such`
  line `persons agreed in the apportionment of the compensation, the particulars of such apportionment shall be`
  line `specified in the award, and as between such persons the award shall be conclusive evidence of the correctness`
  line `of the apportionment.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (43569)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Dispute as to apportionment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43569&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `When the amount of compensation has been settled under`
  line `section 12, if any dispute arises as to the apportionment of the same or any part thereof, or as to the persons to`
  line `whom the same or any part thereof is payable, the Collector may refer such dispute to the decision of the`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (43570)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Payment of compensation or deposit of same in Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43570&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) On making an award under`
  line `section 12, the Collector shall tender payment of the compensation awarded by him to the persons interested`
  line `entitled thereto according to the award, and shall pay it to them unless prevented by some one or more of the`
  line `contingencies mentioned in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) If they do not consent to receive it, or if there is no person competent to alienate the land, or if there is`
  line `any dispute as to the title to receive the compensation or as to the apportionment of it, the Collector shall`
  line `deposit the amount of the compensation in the Court to which a reference under section 18 would be`
  line `submitted:`
  line
  line `Provided, first, that any person admitted to be interested may receive such payment under protest as to the`
  line `sufficiency of the amount:`
  line
  line `Provided, secondly, that no person who has received the amount otherwise than under protest shall be`
  line `entitled to make any application under section 18:`
  line
  line `Provided, thirdly, that nothing herein contained shall affect the liability of any person, who may receive`
  line `the whole or any part of any compensation awarded under this Act, to pay the same to the person lawfully`
  line `entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything in this section, the Collector may, with the sanction of the ^1[CentralGovernment] instead of awarding a money compensation in respect of any land, make any arrangement with`
  line `a person having a limited interest in such land, either by the grant of other lands in exchange, or by the`
  line `remission of land revenue on the same or on other lands held under the same title, or in such other way as`
  line `may be equitable having regard to the interests of the parties concerned.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (3) shall be construed to interfere with or limit the power of the Collector to`
  line `enter into any arrangement with any person interested in the land and competent to contract in respect thereof`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (43571)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Investment of money deposited in respect of lands belonging to persons incompetent to alienate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43571&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any money is deposited in Court under section 31, sub-section (2), and it appears that the`
  line `land in respect of which the same was awarded belonged to any person who had no power to alienate the`
  line `same, the Court shall order the money to be invested--`
  line
  line `(a) in the purchase of other lands to be held under the like title and conditions of ownership as the`
  line `land in respect of which such money was deposited is held, or`
  line
  line `(b) if such purchase cannot be effected forthwith, then in such Government or other approved`
  line `securities as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `and shall direct the payment of the interest or other proceeds arising from such investment to the person or`
  line `persons who would for the time being have been entitled to the possession of the said land, and such moneys`
  line `shall remain so deposited and invested until the same are applied--`
  line
  line `(i) in the purchase of such other lands as aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in payment 16 any person or persons becoming absolutely entitled thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) In all cases of moneys deposited to which this section applies, the Court shall order the cost of the`
  line `following matters, including therein all reasonable charges and expenses incident thereto, to be paid by the`
  line `Collector, namely :--`
  line
  line `(a) the costs of such investment as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(b) the costs of the orders for the payment of the interest or other proceeds of the securities in which`
  line `such moneys are for the time being invested, and for the payment out of Court of the principal of such`
  line `moneys and the costs of all proceedings relating thereto, except such as may be occasioned by litigation`
  line `between adverse claimants.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (43572)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Investment of money deposited in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43572&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `If any money is deposited in Court under this Act`
  line `for any cause other than that mentioned in section 32, the Court may, on the application of any party`
  line `interested or claiming an interest in such money, order the same to be invested in such Government or other`
  line `approved securities as it thinks fit, and may direct the interest or other proceeds of any such investment to be`
  line `accumulated and paid in such manner as will, in its opinion, give the parties interested therein the same`
  line `benefit therefrom as they might have had from the land in respect of which such money was deposited or as`
  line `near thereto as may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (43573)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Payment of interest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43573&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `When the amount of any compensation awarded under this Act is not paid or`
  line `deposited within fifteen days of making the award, the Collector shall pay the amount awarded with interest`
  line `thereon at the rate of six per centum per annum from the date of the award until it is so paid or deposited.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (43574)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Service of notices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43574&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Service of any notice under this Act shall be made by delivering or tendering`
  line `a copy thereof signed, in the case of a notice under section 3, sub-section (2), by the officer therein`
  line `mentioned, and, in the case of any other notice, by or by order of the Collector or the Judge.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever it may be practicable, the service of the notice shall be made on the person therein named.`
  line
  line `(3) When such person cannot be found, the service may be made on any adult male member of his family`
  line `residing with him and, if no such adult male member can be found, the notice may be served by fixing the`
  line `copy on the outer door of the house in which the person therein named ordinarily dwells or carries on`
  line `business, or by fixing a copy thereof in some conspicuous place in the office of the officer aforesaid or of the`
  line `Collector or in the court-house and also in some conspicuous part of the land upon which restrictions are to`
  line `be imposed:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the Collector or Judge so directs, a notice may be sent by post in a letter addressed to the`
  line `person named therein at his last known residence, address or place of business and service of it may he`
  line `proved by the production of the addressee's receipt.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (43575)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43575&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Whoever willfully--`
  line
  line `(a) obstructs any person in doing any of the acts authorised by section 4, section 6 or section 8, or`
  line
  line `(b) destroys, damages, alters or otherwise interferes with the ground level or any work done under`
  line `section 6, or`
  line
  line `(c) contravenes any of the provisions of section 7 or any condition prescribed thereunder,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month or with fine which may`
  line `extend to fifty rupees, or with both, and, in the case of a continuing offence, with an additional fine which`
  line `may extend to five rupees for every day after the first in regard to which he is convicted of having persisted in`
  line `the offence; and any expenses incurred in removing the effects of his offence may be recovered from him in`
  line `the manner provided by the law for the time being in force for the recovery of fines.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (43576)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Magistrate to enforce the terms of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1974, s. 3, for certain words`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43576&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `If the Collector or officer authorised under section 6 is`
  line `opposed or impeded in doing anything directed or permitted by this Act, he shall, if a Magistrate, enforce`
  line `compliance, and, if not a Magistrate, he shall apply to a Magistrate ^1[or (within any area for which a`
  line `Commissioner of Police] has been appointed) to the Commissioner of Police and such Magistrate or`
  line `Commissioner (as the case may be) shall enforce compliance.`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (43584)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Completion of imposition of restrictions not compulsory, but compensation to be awarded when not completed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43584&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[Central Government] shall be at liberty to withdraw from the imposition of`
  line `any declared restrictions before any of the measures authorised by section 6 have been taken.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever the ^1[Central Government] withdraws the imposition of any declared restrictions, the`
  line `Collector shall determine the amount of compensation due for the damage suffered by the owner in`
  line `consequence of the notice or of any proceedings thereunder, and shall pay such amount to the person`
  line `interested, together with all costs reasonably incurred by him in the prosecution of the proceedings under this`
  line `Act relating to the said restrictions.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of Part III shall apply, so far as may be, to the determination of the compensation`
  line `payable under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (43578)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 40
  title `Demolition of part of house or building and imposition of restrictions on part of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L.G.".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43578&sectionno=39&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `provisions of this Act shall not be put in force for the purpose of demolishing or acquiring the right to`
  line `demolish a part only of any house, manufactory or other building, if the owner desires that the whole of such`
  line `house, manufactory or building shall be demolished or that the right to demolish the whole of it shall be`
  line `acquired:`
  line
  line `Provided that the owner may at any time before the Collector has made his award under section 12, by`
  line `notice in writing, withdraw or modify his expressed desire that the whole of such house, manufactory or`
  line `building shall be demolished, or that the right to demolish the whole of it shall be acquired ;`
  line
  line `Provided a lop so, that if any question shall arise as to whether any building or other construction`
  line `proposed to be demolished under this Act does or does not form part of a house, manufactory or building`
  line `within the meaning of this section, the Collector shall refer the determination of such question to the Court,`
  line `and such building or other construction shall not be demolished until after the question has been determined.`
  line
  line `In deciding on such a reference the Court shall have regard to the question whether the building or other`
  line `construction proposed to be demolished is reasonably required for the full and unimpaired use of the house,`
  line `manufactory or building.`
  line
  line `(2) If, in the case of any claim of the kind referred to in section 23, sub-section (1), clause (c), by a person`
  line `interested, on account of ceasing to be able to use the land, upon the use and enjoyment of which restrictions`
  line `are to be imposed, conjointly with his other land, the a ^1[Central Government] is of opinion that the claim is`
  line `unreasonable or excessive, it may, at any time before the Collector has made his award, order the imposition`
  line `of restrictions upon the whole of the land of which the land upon the use and enjoyment of which it was first`
  line `sought to impose restrictions forms a part.`
  line
  line `(3) In the case provided for by sub-section (2) no fresh declaration or other proceeding under sections 3`
  line `to 10 shall be necessary; but the Collector shall without delay furnish a copy of the order of the ^1[CentralGovernment] to the person interested, and shall thereafter proceed to make his award under section 12.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, clause (a), any land, upon the use and enjoyment of`
  line `which restrictions are imposed under this section, may be included in the outer boundary, even though its`
  line `distance from the crest of the outer parapet of the work exceeds two thousand yards.`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (43579)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 41
  title `Exemption from stamp duty and fees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43579&sectionno=40&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No award or agreement made under this Act shall be`
  line `chargeable with stamp duty, and no person claiming under any such award or agreement shall be liable to pay`
  line `any fee for a copy of the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (43580)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 42
  title `Notice in case of suits for anything done in pursuance of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43580&sectionno=41&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other proceeding shall`
  line `be commenced or prosecuted against any person for anything done in pursuance of this Act, without giving to`
  line `such person a months previous notice in writing of the intended proceeding, and of the cause thereof, nor`
  line `after tender of sufficient amends.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (43581)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 43
  title `Code of Civil Procedure to apply to proceedings before Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43581&sectionno=42&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Save in so far as they may be`
  line `inconsistent with anything contained in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure^1(14 of 1882)`
  line `shall apply to all proceedings before the Court under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (43582)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 44
  title `Appeals in proceedings before Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. See now the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43582&sectionno=43&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure^1(14 of 1882) applicable to appeals from original decrees, an appeal shall lie to the High Court`
  line `from the award or from any part of the award of the Court in any proceeding under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (43583)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 45
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572&sectionId=43583&sectionno=44&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00020_190307_1523340006572
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules] for the guidance of officers in all matters connected with the enforcement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to make rules under sub-section (1) shall be subject to the condition of the rules being`
  line `made after previous publication.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following`
  line `the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or`
  line `both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 50 of 1974, s. 4, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (3).`
